dcterms:description: A dataset providing information on ducted wind turbines and their technology, focusing on how ducted designs can improve efficiency and reliability in small wind energy systems.
dcterms:title: Ducted Wind Turbines (DWT)

dcterms:creator: N. Bagheri-Sadeghi
B. T. Helenbrook
K. D. Visser
dcterms:description: This dataset presents findings on the maximal power output per device area for ducted turbines, contributing to the understanding of their efficiency compared to traditional turbines.
dcterms:title: Maximal power per device area of a ducted turbine

dcterms:creator: A. Kummer
J. Dimeo
M. Hebel
K. Visser
dcterms:description: This dataset discusses the application of cambered plate airfoils in small wind turbines, highlighting their potential advantages over conventional airfoils.
dcterms:title: On the Use of Cambered Plate Airfoils for Small Wind Turbines

dcterms:creator: D. N. Valyou
K. D. Visser
dcterms:description: This dataset provides insights into the design considerations necessary for developing small ducted wind turbines, focusing on structural and operational aspects.
dcterms:title: Design considerations for a small ducted wind turbine

dcterms:creator: T. Harris
J. H. Rumbarger
C. P. Butterfield
dcterms:description: This dataset outlines the design guidelines for yaw and pitch rolling bearing life in wind turbines, providing essential information for maintenance and reliability.
dcterms:title: Wind Turbine Design Guideline DG03: Yaw and Pitch Rolling Bearing Life

dcterms:creator: P. He
R. Hong
H. Wang
C. Lu
dcterms:description: This dataset presents an analysis of the fatigue life of slewing bearings used in wind turbines, contributing to the understanding of their reliability and maintenance needs.
dcterms:title: Fatigue life analysis of slewing bearings in wind turbines
